WHAT THIS REPOSITORY IS
-----------------------

A TEACHING SCAFFOLD prepared for the workshop:

    "WS:C2 — From Alert to Action: Building a 5-Agent AI System
     That Cuts MTTR"
     AutoCon5 Munich · Tuesday 2026-06-09 · 09:00–13:00 CET
     Presenter: Eduard Dulharu (vExpertAI)

It demonstrates the architectural pattern of the production
Dream Team agentic NetOps platform — "the catalogue decides what
to investigate, the LLM writes the diagnosis, the human approves
the change" — using a minimal 5-service Docker Compose stack
suitable for a workshop attendee's laptop.


WHAT THIS REPOSITORY IS NOT
---------------------------

This is INTENTIONALLY a simplified mock-up. It does NOT contain
the production system. The following components are proprietary
vExpertAI software and are NOT distributed under this license:

  • The full 72-scenario diagnostic catalogue + 42 diagnostic trees
  • The va-v2 fine-tuned LoRA adapter weights (gate-cleared against
    its base model and gpt-4o-mini on a sealed EVPN exam)
  • The gated-finetuning training methodology + training datasets
  • The production multi-vendor adapter layer
    (Cisco NX-OS / Arista EOS / Nokia SR Linux / Cisco IOS-XE)
  • The 7-pass validation pipeline (Confidence Scorer, Change Risk
    Officer, Digital Twin sandbox, Blast Radius Forecaster, audit
    chain)
  • The DORA/NIS2 compliance mapping (20 reasoning-chain artifacts
    mapped to 8 DORA articles + 6 NIS2 Article 21 sub-sections)
  • The Fabric Architect multi-vendor EVPN-VXLAN audit agent
  • The TimescaleDB HMAC-chained reasoning-chain audit substrate
  • The Neo4j Knowledge Graph schema, seeds, and live-sync code
  • All production deployment automation, infrastructure-as-code,
    secrets management, and operational tooling


